# NatureSip: Application Architecture & Structure

This document outlines the technical design and organizational structure of the NatureSip premium application.

## 1. Technical Stack
- **Frontend Framework:** [Vite](https://vitejs.dev/) + [React](https://reactjs.org/) (JavaScript)
- **Styling:** Vanilla CSS 3 with HSL variables for dynamic theme management.
- **Animations:** [Framer Motion](https://www.framer.com/motion/) for premium micro-interactions and page transitions.
- **Icons:** [Lucide React](https://lucide.dev/) for sleek, consistent iconography.
- **Typography:** 
  - Primary: *Outfit* (Aesthetic & Modern)
  - Secondary: *Inter* (Legibility)

## 2. Design Principles
- **Visual Excellence:** Use of high-quality media, glassmorphism, and smooth gradients.
- **Responsive Design:** Mobile-first approach with fluid layouts.
- **Performance:** Optimized media loading (Lazy loading, WebP format where possible).
- **Branding:** Consistent use of Forest Green (#2D5A27) and Gold accents to convey a premium organic feel.

## 3. Directory Structure
```text
naturesip_media/
├── public/                 # Static assets
├── src/
│   ├── assets/
│   │   ├── media/          # Downloaded product photos/videos
│   │   └── styles/         # Global CSS and themes
│   ├── components/         # Reusable UI components
│   │   ├── PremiumHeader/
│   │   ├── ProductCard/
│   │   └── ProcessTimeline/
│   ├── sections/           # High-level page sections
│   │   ├── Hero/
│   │   ├── Catalog/
│   │   └── Manufacturing/
│   ├── App.jsx             # Main application logic
│   └── main.jsx            # Entry point
├── docs/                   # Production/Manufacturing documentation
├── package.json
└── vite.config.js
```

## 4. End-to-End Planning
- **Phase 1: Asset Procurement** (Fetching media from harikripa-naturesip.lovable.app)
- **Phase 2: Core UI Development** (Implementing the Premium Design System)
- **Phase 3: Integration** (Populating components with real product data and media)
- **Phase 4: Optimization** (Final polish and performance tuning)
